              <div class="appointment-timeline">
                <div class="timeline-step">
                  <div class="step-number">1</div>
                  <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Initial Consultation (5-10 minutes)</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Discussion of symptoms and medical history</li>
                      <li>Review of current medications</li>
                      <li>Questions about previous ear problems</li>
                      <li>Explanation of the treatment process</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-step">
                  <div class="step-number">2</div>
                  <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Examination (5 minutes)</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Otoscopic examination of both ears</li>
                      <li>Assessment of wax type and location</li>
                      <li>Check for any contraindications</li>
                      <li>Selection of appropriate treatment method</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-step">
                  <div class="step-number">3</div>
                  <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Treatment (15-25 minutes)</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Professional microsuction or irrigation</li>
                      <li>Careful removal under direct visualisation</li>
                      <li>Regular checks during the process</li>
                      <li>Immediate hearing improvement assessment</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="timeline-step">
                  <div class="step-number">4</div>
                  <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Post-Treatment (5-10 minutes)</h4>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Final examination of treated ears</li>
                      <li>Aftercare instructions provided</li>
                      <li>Questions answered</li>
                      <li>Follow-up arrangements if needed</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="appointment-total">
                <strong>Total appointment time: 30-50 minutes</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What's the difference between microsuction and irrigation?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Both are professional methods, but they work differently:</p>
              <div class="method-comparison">
                <div class="method-card microsuction">
                  <h4>üî¨ Microsuction</h4>
                  <div class="method-details">
                    <p><strong>How it works:</strong> Uses gentle suction under microscopic vision to remove wax</p>
                    <div class="method-specs">
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Safety:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value excellent">Excellent</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Comfort:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value excellent">Very comfortable</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Effectiveness:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value excellent">Highly effective</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Duration:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value">15-25 minutes</span>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="method-benefits">
                      <h5>Best For:</h5>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Hard, impacted wax</li>
                        <li>People with perforated eardrums</li>
                        <li>Hearing aid users</li>
                        <li>Those who prefer dry methods</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="method-card irrigation">
                  <h4>üíß Ear Irrigation</h4>
                  <div class="method-details">
                    <p><strong>How it works:</strong> Uses controlled warm water flow to flush out wax</p>
                    <div class="method-specs">
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Safety:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value good">Very good</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Comfort:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value good">Comfortable</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Effectiveness:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value good">Effective</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="spec-item">
                        <span class="spec-label">Duration:</span>
                        <span class="spec-value">10-20 minutes</span>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="method-benefits">
                      <h5>Best For:</h5>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Soft to medium wax</li>
                        <li>People comfortable with water</li>
                        <li>Quick removal needed</li>
                        <li>Cost-conscious patients</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do I need to prepare for my appointment?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Preparation depends on your chosen treatment method:</p>
              <div class="preparation-guide">
                <div class="prep-section">
                  <h4>üî¨ For Microsuction</h4>
                  <div class="prep-list">
                    <h5>‚úÖ Usually No Preparation Needed</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Microsuction works effectively on all wax types</li>
                      <li>Come as you are - no advance preparation</li>
                      <li>Can be performed immediately</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>üìã Optional (if very hard wax)</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Use olive oil drops for 2-3 days beforehand</li>
                      <li>This can make removal more comfortable</li>
                      <li>Your practitioner will advise if needed</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="prep-section">
                  <h4>üíß For Irrigation</h4>
                  <div class="prep-list">
                    <h5>üìù Preparation Usually Required</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>Use softening drops for 3-5 days</strong> before appointment</li>
                      <li>Apply drops 2-3 times daily as directed</li>
                      <li>Options: olive oil, mineral oil, or commercial drops</li>
                      <li>This is essential for safe, effective irrigation</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h5>‚ö†Ô∏è Important</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Don't skip the softening phase</li>
                      <li>Your clinic will provide specific instructions</li>
                      <li>Appointment may need rescheduling if not prepared</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="general-prep">
                <h4>üìã General Preparation for All Appointments</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Bring photo ID and payment method</li>
                  <li>List current medications</li>
                  <li>Note any ear surgery history</li>
                  <li>Bring hearing aids (if worn)</li>
                  <li>Arrive 10 minutes early</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long do the results last?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Results vary significantly between individuals:</p>
              <div class="duration-ranges">
                <div class="duration-item">
                  <h4>üë• Most People</h4>
                  <div class="duration-detail">
                    <span class="duration-time">6-12 months</span>
                    <p>Normal wax production, occasional mild symptoms</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="duration-item">
                  <h4>üîÑ Frequent Producers</h4>
                  <div class="duration-detail">
                    <span class="duration-time">3-6 months</span>
                    <p>Higher wax production, regular buildup issues</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="duration-item">
                  <h4>üëÇ Hearing Aid Users</h4>
                  <div class="duration-detail">
                    <span class="duration-time">2-4 months</span>
                    <p>Devices can stimulate production and block natural migration</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="duration-item">
                  <h4>üè≠ High-Risk Environments</h4>
                  <div class="duration-detail">
                    <span class="duration-time">1-3 months</span>
                    <p>Dusty work, frequent earplug use, swimming</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="duration-factors">
                <h4>Factors Affecting Duration:</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Individual wax production rate</strong> (genetic)</li>
                  <li><strong>Ear canal anatomy</strong> (shape and size)</li>
                  <li><strong>Environmental exposure</strong> (dust, debris)</li>
                  <li><strong>Hearing aid use</strong> (blocks natural migration)</li>
                  <li><strong>Age</strong> (wax becomes harder with age)</li>
                  <li><strong>Skin conditions</strong> (eczema increases production)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="safety-pain" class="faq-section">
        <h2>üõ°Ô∏è Safety & Pain</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is ear wax removal painful?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Professional ear wax removal should not be painful when performed correctly:</p>
              <div class="pain-levels">
                <div class="pain-method">
                  <h4>üî¨ Microsuction</h4>
                  <div class="pain-rating">
                    <span class="pain-score">1-2/10</span>
                    <span class="pain-description">Minimal discomfort</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pain-details">
                    <h5>What you might feel:</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Gentle suction sensation</li>
                      <li>Slight tickling or pressure</li>
                      <li>Occasional mild discomfort if wax is very hard</li>
                      <li>Immediate relief as blockage clears</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Most patients describe it as:</strong> "Slightly odd sensation, but not painful at all"</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="pain-method">
                  <h4>üíß Irrigation</h4>
                  <div class="pain-rating">
                    <span class="pain-score">1-3/10</span>
                    <span class="pain-description">Mild discomfort possible</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pain-details">
                    <h5>What you might feel:</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Warm water sensation</li>
                      <li>Fullness as water fills the ear</li>
                      <li>Brief dizziness from temperature or pressure</li>
                      <li>Relief as wax is flushed out</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Most patients describe it as:</strong> "Like having a shower in your ear"</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="pain-management">
                <h4>üåü Comfort Measures</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Tell your practitioner if you feel any discomfort</li>
                  <li><strong>Breaks:</strong> Procedures can be paused at any time</li>
                  <li><strong>Technique adjustment:</strong> Pressure and speed can be modified</li>
                  <li><strong>Alternative methods:</strong> Switch techniques if needed</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="pain-warning">
                <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è When to Expect Some Discomfort</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Very hard, long-standing impacted wax</li>
                  <li>Sensitive or inflamed ear canals</li>
                  <li>First-time treatment anxiety</li>
                  <li>Very narrow ear canals</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Remember:</strong> Any significant pain is not normal. Your practitioner will stop and reassess if you experience real discomfort.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Are there any risks or side effects?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Professional ear wax removal is very safe when performed by qualified practitioners:</p>
              <div class="risk-assessment">
                <div class="risk-category low-risk">
                  <h4>‚úÖ Most Common (Normal & Temporary)</h4>
                  <div class="risk-list">
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>Temporary sensitivity</strong> to sounds (few hours)</li>
                      <li><strong>Mild ear canal irritation</strong> (24-48 hours)</li>
                      <li><strong>Slight dizziness</strong> during irrigation (minutes)</li>
                      <li><strong>Hearing feels "different"</strong> initially (normal adjustment)</li>
                      <li><strong>Minor ear fullness</strong> from swelling (1-2 days)</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="risk-category moderate-risk">
                  <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è Uncommon but Possible</h4>
                  <div class="risk-list">
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>Outer ear infection</strong> (if water trapped after irrigation)</li>
                      <li><strong>Temporary tinnitus</strong> (ringing) - usually resolves quickly</li>
                      <li><strong>Nausea</strong> from stimulation of balance organs</li>
                      <li><strong>Incomplete removal</strong> requiring follow-up</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Incidence:</strong> Less than 5% of treatments</p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="risk-category serious-risk">
                  <h4>üö® Serious Complications (Very Rare)</h4>
                  <div class="risk-list">
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>Eardrum perforation</strong> (hole in eardrum)</li>
                      <li><strong>Inner ear damage</strong> (affects hearing or balance)</li>
                      <li><strong>Facial nerve injury</strong> (extremely rare)</li>
                      <li><strong>Severe infection</strong> requiring antibiotics</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>Incidence:</strong> Less than 0.1% when performed by qualified practitioners</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="risk-reduction">
                <h4>üõ°Ô∏è How We Minimise Risks</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Qualified practitioners:</strong> HCPC registered audiologists</li>
                  <li><strong>Proper assessment:</strong> Pre-treatment examination</li>
                  <li><strong>Appropriate technique:</strong> Method selection based on your needs</li>
                  <li><strong>Sterile equipment:</strong> Single-use or properly sterilised instruments</li>
                  <li><strong>Direct visualisation:</strong> Microscopes and otoscopes for safety</li>
                  <li><strong>Patient monitoring:</strong> Constant communication during treatment</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Who shouldn't have ear wax removal?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Most people can safely have professional ear wax removal, but some conditions require special consideration:</p>
              <div class="contraindications">
                <div class="contraindication-category absolute">
                  <h4>üö´ Absolute Contraindications (Do Not Treat)</h4>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Active ear infection</strong> with pain, discharge, or fever</li>
                    <li><strong>Acute ear canal inflammation</strong> (severe otitis externa)</li>
                    <li><strong>Recent ear surgery</strong> (within 6 weeks without ENT clearance)</li>
                    <li><strong>Known eardrum perforation</strong> (irrigation contraindicated)</li>
                    <li><strong>Severe bleeding disorders</strong> or anticoagulation issues</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="contraindication-category relative">
                  <h4>‚ö†Ô∏è Relative Contraindications (Caution Required)</h4>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Previous ear surgery</strong> (may need ENT specialist referral)</li>
                    <li><strong>History of eardrum perforation</strong> (microsuction preferred)</li>
                    <li><strong>Severe balance disorders</strong> (may worsen symptoms)</li>
                    <li><strong>Anxiety about procedures</strong> (may need sedation discussion)</li>
                    <li><strong>Children under 6</strong> (specialist paediatric care recommended)</li>
                    <li><strong>Pregnancy</strong> (generally safe but needs discussion)</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="contraindication-category special">
                  <h4>üè• Special Considerations</h4>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Hearing aids:</strong> Can usually be treated (inform practitioner)</li>
                    <li><strong>Diabetes:</strong> Higher infection risk, extra care needed</li>
                    <li><strong>Immunocompromised:</strong> Sterile technique critical</li>
                    <li><strong>Blood thinners:</strong> Discuss with practitioner first</li>
                    <li><strong>Very elderly patients:</strong> May need gentler approaches</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="assessment-note">
                <h4>üìã Pre-Treatment Assessment</h4>
                <p>All reputable clinics will assess your suitability before treatment. This includes:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Medical history review</li>
                  <li>Otoscopic examination</li>
                  <li>Discussion of any concerns</li>
                  <li>Treatment method selection</li>
                  <li>Informed consent process</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

